"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Basic.html#Rat.toDyadic\">toDyadic</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">prec</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `y : Dyadic` has precision at most `prec` and a rational `q` lies in the half-open\ninterval `[y.toRat, y.toRat + 2 ^ (-prec))`, then `y` is the floor of `q` at precision\n`prec`, i.e. `y = q.toDyadic prec`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.eq_toDyadic_of_precision_le","kind":"theorem","line":55,"name":"Dyadic.eq_toDyadic_of_precision_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.lean#L55-L92"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.invAtPrec_eq_divAtPrec_one\"><span class=\"name\">Dyadic</span>.<span class=\"name\">invAtPrec_eq_divAtPrec_one</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Basic.html#Dyadic\">Dyadic</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">prec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.invAtPrec\">invAtPrec</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">prec</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.divAtPrec\">divAtPrec</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">prec</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`invAtPrec x prec` is the special case `divAtPrec 1 x prec` of dyadic division. ","docLink":"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.invAtPrec_eq_divAtPrec_one","kind":"theorem","line":45,"name":"Dyadic.invAtPrec_eq_divAtPrec_one","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.lean#L45-L53"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.divAtPrec\"><span class=\"name\">Dyadic</span>.<span class=\"name\">divAtPrec</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Basic.html#Dyadic\">Dyadic</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">prec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Basic.html#Dyadic\">Dyadic</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Divides two dyadic numbers at a given (maximum) precision.\nReturns the greatest dyadic number with precision at most `prec` which is less than or equal\nto `a/b`. For `b = 0`, returns `0`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.divAtPrec","kind":"def","line":35,"name":"Dyadic.divAtPrec","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.lean#L35-L43"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.invAtPrec\"><span class=\"name\">Dyadic</span>.<span class=\"name\">invAtPrec</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Basic.html#Dyadic\">Dyadic</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">prec</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Basic.html#Dyadic\">Dyadic</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Inverts a dyadic number at a given (maximum) precision.\nReturns the greatest dyadic number with precision at most `prec` which is less than or equal to `1/x`.\nFor `x = 0`, returns `0`.\n\nThis agrees with `divAtPrec 1 x prec` (see `invAtPrec_eq_divAtPrec_one`), but is kept as a\nseparate definition to avoid the unnecessary `1 *`-by-numerator step in `Rat`'s division at\nruntime.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.html#Dyadic.invAtPrec","kind":"def","line":21,"name":"Dyadic.invAtPrec","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Dyadic/Inv.lean#L21-L33"}}],"imports":["Init.Data.Dyadic.Basic","Init.Data.Int.Order","Init.Data.Rat.Lemmas"],"instances":[],"name":"Init.Data.Dyadic.Inv"}